One of the sunniest regions in BC's Lower Mainland, Delta embraces three unique communities - Ladner, North Delta and Tsawwassen. The City of Delta is looking for dedicated individuals to join our team and share in our commitment to lead the way in public service excellence. 
 City of Delta  Engineering Summer Student (Special Projects)

  Job Location: Delta, British Columbia, Canada Term: Approximately 4 months (May to August 2024) Hours of work: 32 hours per week Applicable disciplines within the above departments: CIVIL  Delta is a vibrant municipality that is rich in soil and water, rich in history and industry, and especially rich in people. Situated in the “delta” of the Fraser River, Delta is home to a population of more than 108,000 residents. With the support of a strong farming and agricultural foundation, we pride ourselves on our past and our sustainable future.  We have an exciting opportunity for a co-op/summer student to join the Engineering department. The successful candidate will work in a supportive team with the opportunity to attain a broad range of engineering experience including utilities, development, transportation, steep slopes and flood protection.  Under the general direction of the Engineering Services Manager, you will be responsible for the following assignments: 

  Reviewing highway use permits for third-party utilities; 
  Coordinating third party utility relocations; 
  Reviewing traffic management plans; 
  Researching and drafting utilities-related Bylaw amendments to support future growth; 
  Preparing an inventory of Delta’s seawalls; 
  Preparing a master cost estimate spreadsheet for municipal infrastructure; 
  Assisting with reviewing development-related drawings, reports, and analyses and providing feedback to your superior; and 
  Performing a variety of inspections and tasks when needed.

   Desirable Training and Experience: 

  Excellent written and verbal communication skills; 
  Strong customer service skills; 
  Skilled in the use of Microsoft Outlook, Word, Excel, and PowerPoint; 
  Experience with AutoCAD would be an asset; and, 
  Ability to work independently with minimal supervision.

   Required Licences: 

  A valid Class 5 BC Driver’s License is required.

  Preference will be given to applicants currently enrolled in an undergraduate program with a focus on civil engineering studies. Previous experience related to development, construction, utilities and/or municipal engineering services would be an asset.  The City of Delta provides a competitive salary of $25.93 per hour +12% in lieu of benefits. Interested applicants are requested to apply online at www.delta.ca/employment to competition number 24-79 EX by March 14, 2024.  The City of Delta's Covid-19 Vaccination policy has been suspended, however, we reserve the right to reinstate it in response to changes in the public health landscape, including public health orders. We are committed to the protection, health, and safety of our employees and our community, and our Communicable Disease Plan and related protocols remain in place.  We thank all applicants for their interest; only those under consideration will be contacted. Copies of relevant professional certificates, degrees, or tickets must be submitted with your application. Preferred candidates will be required to submit a Police Information Check.

